    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2018-03-20</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2018-05-31T19:32:29Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Every Person Counts Act</b></p> <p>This bill modifies provisions regarding population and other census information to: (1) require that there be a tabulation of the total number of persons in each state, and (2) prohibit the Bureau of the Census from including any question or otherwise eliciting any information regarding U.S citizenship or immigration status.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Every Person Counts Act</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
        <titleType>Display Title</titleType>
        <title>Every Person Counts Act</title>
      </item>
      <item>
        <titleType>Official Title as Introduced</titleType>
        <title>A bill to amend title 13, United States Code, to make clear that each decennial census, as required for the apportionment of Representatives in Congress among the several States, shall tabulate the total number of persons in each State, and to provide that no information regarding United States citizenship or immigration status may be elicited in any such census.</title>
        <billTextVersionName>Introduced in Senate</billTextVersionName>
        <billTextVersionCode>IS</billTextVersionCode>
      </item>
